CNCP v1 24916
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#12246: Dupliucate ref in template with v-if checking for the ref leads to a recursion error",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:21:55.448358+00:00",
  "text": "Dupliucate ref in template with v-if checking for the ref leads to a recursion error\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.5.12\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nUse a ref on at least two elements, outside of a v-for, in order to create a referenced element. The last element in the DOM will be the referenced element. Add a v-if check on another element for the ref-element. \r\n\r\nThis is the same code as in the minimal reproduction:\r\n```vue\r\n<script setup>\r\nimport { ref } from 'vue'\r\n\r\nconst test = ref()\r\n</script>\r\n<template>\r\n  <span ref=\"test\">test 1</span>\r\n  <span ref=\"test\">test 2</span>\r\n  <div v-if=\"test\">\r\n    test 3\r\n  </div>\r\n</template>\r\n\r\n```\n\n### What is expected?\n\nI was expecting for the code to work without any error messages, or give an error message that is possible to understand. \n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nUncaught (in promise): Maximum recursive updates exceeded in component <Repl>. This means you have a reactive effect that is mutating its own dependencies and thus recursively triggering itself. Possible sources include component template, render function, updated hook or watcher source function.\n\n### System Info\n\n_No response_\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\nIt is not clear why this leads to a recursion error, and that makes it hard to debug when you accidentally end up in this situation.\r\n\r\nI think a good solution to this problem would be to throw another exception than a Recursion here. Perhaps something like \"Duplicate referenced element outside of v-for\"? Or perhaps it could \"just work\", like it does if you [wrap the referenced element in a computed, like this](https://play.vuejs.org/#):\r\n\r\n```vue\r\n<script setup>\r\nimport { computed, ref } from 'vue'\r\n\r\nconst test = ref()\r\nconst test2 = computed(() => test.value)\r\n</script>\r\n<template>\r\n  <span ref=\"test\">test 1</span>\r\n  <span ref=\"test\">test 2</span>\r\n  <div v-if=\"test2\">\r\n    test 3\r\n  </div>\r\n</template>\r\n```",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "has workaround",
    "🔩 p2-edge-case"
  ],
